00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:07,360
And their module is the event that aims

484
00:28:07,360 --> 00:28:11,640
to help draw attention to transgender issues

485
00:28:11,640 --> 00:28:13,880
through a topic-focused Ag Day.

486
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:17,560
And for example, the latest events

487
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:22,280
was PyLondonium at London, UK.

488
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:26,120
And their website is transcode.github.io.

489
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:29,680
That's the kind of event that they organize.

490
00:28:29,680 --> 00:28:32,360
It's the creation of the trans.tech,

491
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:34,460
the previous version of the website.

492
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:38,880
And I think that the most popular community

493
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:41,160
is the Django Girls.

494
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:43,400
And their module is we inspire women

495
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:45,480
to fall in love with programming.

496
00:28:46,440 --> 00:28:49,480
And I will not give you the full list

497
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:53,120
because they made a lot of events,

498
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:57,680
more than 700 events in Cameroon, Finland, France,

499
00:28:57,680 --> 00:29:00,800
Ghana, India, Japan, Spain, Switzerland,

500
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:02,600
and many other countries.

501
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:04,720
Their website is DjangoGirl.com.

502
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:09,040
So you can see that all people enjoy programming,

503
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:10,520
so it's very successful.

504
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:12,760
And to conclude,

505
00:29:15,280 --> 00:29:18,880
I would say that we are aware that there is an issue,

506
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:21,440
and we are aware that the core developers

507
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:25,240
is a bottleneck of the development of Python.

508
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:30,240
We are aware that Python has a people issue.

509
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:35,120
And we saw that the mentoring is efficient

510
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:37,720
to train contributors of future core developers.

511
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:39,520
And also that the code of conduct

512
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:41,840
reduces the toxicity of a community.

513
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,960
According to Grido Van Rossum,

514
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:49,920
increasing the core's diversity is a very important goal

515
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:52,560
to ensure the future health of Python.

516
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:58,000
And I like the quote from Brett Cannon,

517
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:00,200
also Naomi Seder, which is,

518
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:02,760
come for the language and stay for the community.

519
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:07,760
So what's next for the diversity and mentoring?

